{
  "texts": [
    "Whereas the Fraunhofer Society is an applied research organization prioritizing relevant technologies and transferring its findings, the institutions in the Leibniz Association address problems that have societal and international relevance.",
    "The Max Planck Society is most active in basic research, and the Helmholtz Association develops and operates complex research infrastructures.",
    "(4) Team size: We calculated the team size per author as the average of the number of coauthors per paper within the observation period.",
    "For the comparison of the five HCR variants, we took the average of this number per variant and publication year.",
    "The third part in the following results section deals with the application of the different HCR variants in a certain context."
  ]
}